en:environmental-score-origins-of-ingred.description:en: Origins of ingredients are one of the Environmental Score components. They are currently extracted from the ingredient list and the Origins field.

en:environmental-score-packaging-packagi.description:en: No packaging data - Packaging is one of the components of the Environmental Score, and thus it's important to have packaging data.

en:gs1-coupon-common-currency-area-prefi.description:en: This product has a barcode with a GS1 coupon common currency area prefix. This is likely a food data quality error as it indicates that the barcode is associated with a coupon rather than a food product.

en:gs1-coupon-prefix.description:en: This product has a barcode which has the format of a GS1 coupon prefix. This is probably a test by someone who scanned a coupon barcode, and added it to Open Food Facts.

en:gs1-future-coupon-prefix.description:en: This product has a barcode with a GS1 future coupon prefix. This is likely a food data quality error as it indicates that the barcode is associated with a coupon that is not yet valid or has expired, rather than a food product.

en:gs1-isbn-prefix.description:en: The International Standard Book Number -ISBN- is for books. In other terms, this is not food, and this should be moved to Open Products Facts by inputting OPF in the Categories field.

en:gs1-issn-prefix.description:en: The International Standard Serial Number -ISSN- is for serial publications. In other terms, this is not food, and this should be moved to Open Products Facts by inputting OPF in the Categories field.

en:gs1-refund-prefix.description:en: This product has a barcode with a GS1 refund prefix. This is likely a food data quality error as it indicates that the barcode is associated with a refund rather than a food product.

en:gs1-warnings.description:en: Data quality warnings linked to GS1 format -producers imports-

en:high-fibres-label-claim-but-fibre-bel.description:en: In EU, a claim that a food is high in fibre may only be made where the product contains at least 6 g of fibre per 100 g or at least 3 g of fibre per 100 kcal. See: https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX%3A02006R1924-20141213

en:high-in-biotin-label-claim-but-biotin.description:en: In EU, claim that a food is a source of vitamins and/or minerals may only be made where the product contains at least a significant amount as defined in the Annex to Directive 90/496/EEC. See: https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX%3A32024L1438

en:high-in-calcium-label-claim-but-calci.description:en: In EU, claim that a food is a source of vitamins and/or minerals may only be made where the product contains at least a significant amount as defined in the Annex to Directive 90/496/EEC. See: https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX%3A32024L1438

en:high-in-iodine-label-claim-but-iodine.description:en: In EU, claim that a food is a source of vitamins and/or minerals may only be made where the product contains at least a significant amount as defined in the Annex to Directive 90/496/EEC. See: https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX%3A32024L1438

en:high-in-iron-label-claim-but-iron-bel.description:en: In EU, claim that a food is a source of vitamins and/or minerals may only be made where the product contains at least a significant amount as defined in the Annex to Directive 90/496/EEC. en:high-in-magnesium-label-claim-but-mag.description:en: In EU, claim that a food is a source of vitamins and/or minerals may only be made where the product contains at least a significant amount as defined in the Annex to Directive 90/496/EEC. See: https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX%3A32024L1438

en:high-in-omega-3-label-claim-but-ala-o.description:en: In EU, a claim that a food is high in omega-3 may only be made where the product contains at least 06 g alpha-linolenic acid per 100 g and per 100 kcal, or at least 80 mg of the sum of eicosapentaenoic acid and docosahexaenoic acid per 100 g and per 100 kcal. See: https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX%3A02006R1924-20141213

en:high-in-pantothenic-acid-label-claim-.description:en: In EU, claim that a food is a source of vitamins and/or minerals may only be made where the product contains at least a significant amount as defined in the Annex to Directive 90/496/EEC. See: https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX%3A32024L1438

en:high-in-phosphore-label-claim-but-pho.description:en: In EU, claim that a food is a source of vitamins and/or minerals may only be made where the product contains at least a significant amount as defined in the Annex to Directive 90/496/EEC. See: https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX%3A32024L1438

en:high-in-zinc-label-claim-but-zinc-bel.description:en: In EU, claim that a food is a source of vitamins and/or minerals may only be made where the product contains at least a significant amount as defined in the Annex to Directive 90/496/EEC. See: https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX%3A32024L1438

en:high-monounsaturated-fat-label-claim-.description:en: In EU, a claim that a food is high in monounsaturated fat may only be made where at least 45 % of the fatty acids present in the product derive from monounsaturated fat under the condition that monounsaturated fat provides more than 20 % of energy of the product. See: https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX%3A02006R1924-20141213
en:high-monounsaturated-fat-label-claim-.description:es: En la UE, solo se puede afirmar que un alimento es rico en grasas monoinsaturadas si al menos el 45 % de los cidos grasos presentes en el producto provienen de grasas monoinsaturadas, siempre y cuando las grasas monoinsaturadas aporten ms del 20 % de la energa del producto. Ver: https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/ES/TXT/?uri=CELEX%3A02006R1924-20141213
en:high-monounsaturated-fat-label-claim-.description:fr: Dans l'UE, une allgation selon laquelle un aliment est riche en acides gras monoinsaturs ne peut tre faite que si au moins 45 % des acides gras prsents dans le produit proviennent d'acides gras monoinsaturs,  condition que les acides gras monoinsaturs fournissent plus de 20 % de l'nergie du produit. Voir: https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/FR/TXT/?uri=CELEX%3A02006R1924-20141213

en:high-proteins-label-claim-but-protein.description:en: In EU, a claim that a food is high in protein may only be made where at least 20 % of the energy value of the food is provided by protein. See: https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX%3A02006R1924-20141213

en:iodine-source-label-claim-but-iodine-.description:en: In EU, claim that a food is a source of vitamins and/or minerals may only be made where the product contains at least a significant amount as defined in the Annex to Directive 90/496/EEC. en:low-energy-label-claim-but-energy-abo.description:en: In EU, a claim that a food is low in energy may only be made where the product does not contain more than 40 kcal or 170 kJ /100 g for solids or more than 20 kcal or 80 kJ /100 ml for liquids. See: https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX%3A02006R1924-20141213

en:low-fat-label-claim-but-fat-above-lim.description:en: In EU, a claim that a food is low fat may only be made where the product contains no more than 3 g of fat per 100 g for solids or 15 g of fat per 100 ml for liquids. 18 g of fat per 100 ml for semi-skimmed milk. See: https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX%3A02006R1924-20141213

en:low-saturated-fat-label-claim-but-fat.description:en: In EU, a claim that a food is fat free may only be made if the sum of saturated fatty acids and trans-fatty acids in the product does not exceed 15 g per 100 g for solids or 075 g/100 ml for liquids and in either case the sum of saturated fatty acids and trans-fatty acids must not provide more than 10 % of energy. See: https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX%3A02006R1924-20141213

en:low-sodium-or-low-salt-label-claim-bu.description:en: In EU, a claim that a food is low sodium or low salt may only be made where the product contains no more than 012 g of sodium, or the equivalent value for salt, per 100 g or per 100 ml. See: https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX%3A02006R1924-20141213

en:low-sugar-label-claim-but-sugar-above.description:en: In EU, a claim that a food is low sugar may only be made where the product contains no more than 5 g of sugars per 100 g for solids or 25 g of sugars per 100 ml for liquids. See: https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=CELEX%3A02006R1924-20141213
